def duplicatePairs(nums, k):         # sliding window O(N)
    seen, res = set(), 0
    i = j = len(nums) - 1
    while i >= 0:                    # prepare to expand the window till containing k duplicate pairs
        if nums[i] in seen:
            k -= 1
            seen.remove(nums[i])
        else:
            seen.add(nums[i])
        while not k:                 # prepare to shrink the window when containing k duplicate pairs
            res += i + 1
            if nums[j] in seen:
                seen.remove(nums[j])
            else:
                k += 1
                seen.add(nums[j])
            j -= 1                   # ready to shrink
        i -= 1                       # ready to expand
    return res

**This the solution which gave the score of 254/300 

void findValue(vector<int> v, int k)
{
   int i = 0, c = 0;
    int n = v.size();

while (i < n)
{
    int j = i, c1 = 0;
    unordered_map<int, int> mp;
    while (j < n)
    {
        mp[v[j]]++;
        if (mp[v[j]] == 2)
        {
            c1++;
            mp[v[j]] = 0;
        }
        if (c1 >= k)
            c++;
        j++;
    }

    i++;
}
cout << c;

}
